    <PrimAttribute name="autoLoadPlanAt3Height" id="c899b52b-e6b7-4a00-9b5d-cc823a98b70b">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="Boolean"/>
        <access>protected</access>
        <text>
Terminal Config flag : 'Auto Load Plan Split Row At Top Height'

If this is set then they want it to check whether the top height items in the same row are mixed, i.e. diff voy or discharge port.
if they are then we do not do normal row end seperation instead we plan the top height  in order from either end.</text>
    </PrimAttribute>
